 That's the first thing you do.

260
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:49,360
 If you wanna build a trusting relationship with God,

261
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:52,540
 then you need to come honest to him.

262
00:09:52,540 --> 00:09:53,640
 By this point, it's important to know,

263
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:55,180
 like, Abram was probably a few years

264
00:09:55,180 --> 00:09:56,240
 into his journey with God,

265
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,720
 and yet, despite having lived

266
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,920
 through some pretty wild circumstances,

267
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:02,000
 like, by this point, he has left his home,

268
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,360
 he has left his family,

269
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:05,740
 he has faced a famine in this foreign land,

270
00:10:05,740 --> 00:10:08,020
 he has encountered foreign armies,

271
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:11,300
 he is currently in conflict with the king of Sodom.

272
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:13,900
 Despite all of this, and having done it

273
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:16,600
 for the sake of being faithful to God's promise,

274
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:21,920
 he looks up, and he still has no kid to show for it.

275
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:23,520
 Like, the very thing that God said would come,

276
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:26,600
 he doesn't have, and so he comes to God,

277
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:29,080
 and he doesn't do what many of us do

278
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,080
 whenever we find, you know what,

279
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,800
 my circumstances aren't what I expect.

280
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,440
 Like, when things go sideways,

281
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,560
 he doesn't do the Christian game,

282
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,100
 he doesn't put on a right face,

283
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:39,240
 or decide to say the right words,

284
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,080
 or do the right thing.

285
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:42,920
 Instead, what Abram does is he comes real.

286
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:45,040
 He gets really honest.

287
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:47,080
 Have you ever done that before?

288
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,520
 Just got real honest with God

289
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:51,260
 about the things in your life that are frustrating,

290
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:53,980
 that are irritating, that are aggravating,

291
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:55,320
 that you can't make any sense of?

292
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,240
 You ever done that?

293
00:10:56,240 --> 00:11:00,200
 I know I just did that a couple of weeks ago,

294
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,200
 I got in prep for this message, and yet,

295
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,080
 it just ironically set this up,

296
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,640
 so that way the text applied to me personally,

297
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,280
 but a couple weeks ago, I was driving back

298
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:10,560
 from Ouachita Baptist University.

299
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,460
 You really gotta emphasize the Ouach.

300
00:11:12,460 --> 00:11:16,800
 Because the people know, you know, the Tigers,

301
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:20,080
 they live four hours up in Arkadelphia, Arkansas,

302
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,720
 and so I made my way up there to speak at a chapel,

303
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,340
 and it was a joy, it was so great to be there,

304
00:11:24,340 --> 00:11:26,400
 and yet on my drive home,

305
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:29,680
 I just felt this agitation in my spirit.

306
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:30,520
 There were some things

307
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:33,020
 that I needed to personally unpack with God,

308
00:11:33,020 --> 00:11:34,400
 some frustrations that I had,

309
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,560
 and so what I decided was,

310
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:37,040
 I'm not gonna turn on the music,

311
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,880
 I'm not gonna download the pod,

312
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:41,440
 I'm just gonna spend time with God and unpack this,

313
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,720
 and then once that's done,

314
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:46,360
 I can go about my merry way and do whatever else I want,

315
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:48,540
 and yet what you realize is by the end of my trip,

316
00:11:48,540 --> 00:11:50,620
 I had gone four hours in complete silence

317
00:11:50,620 --> 00:11:55,440
 because I had just been word-vomiting everything to him.

318
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:57,640
 Now, I don't say that to you

319
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:59,300
 because I'm trying to make myself out

320
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:00,520
 to be some sort of example.

321
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:03,440
 I say that to you because I want you to learn

322
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:06,600
 from my experience that bottling all of that up for so long,

323
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,900
 it took me four hours to unwind

324
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:11,120
 when that never had to be the case,

325
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:13,400
 but I was unwilling to come honest.

326
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,320
 God doesn't want you to be that way.

327
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:18,000
 Like, whatever it is, he wants you to know

328
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,880
 you can come to him on it, and here's the thing.

329
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:24,680
 I think so often we fear if we do come real,

330
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:27,640
 God's gonna want to check the return policy on you and I,

331
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:28,720
 and yet that's just not the case.

332
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,400
 Like, you're not gonna come and tell him something

333
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:31,580
 that he hasn't already known about.

334
00:12:31,580 --> 00:12:33,840
 He's omniscient, he knows everything,

335
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:35,280
 and so he's not gonna turn to the left and be like,

336
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:37,200
 "Gabriel, hold on, man, what did we bite off here?

337
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,840
 "It seems like it's a little bit more than we can chew."

338
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:41,640
 He's gonna look at you and be like, "I know!"

339
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:43,640
 And yet though God knows everything,

340
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:46,760
 he wants to hear about everything from you

341
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:50,600
 because that's what relationship looks like.

342
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:53,960
 So all that sadness you feel about your singleness

343
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:56,400
 because by this point you thought you'd be married,

344
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,120
 you'd have a family, you'd moved on with your life,

345
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,200
 he wants to hear about that.

346
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,600
 Like, all that frustration you feel with your parents

347
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,160
 because no matter how hard you try or how much you give,

348
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,600
 it's still never enough,

349
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,000
 they're perpetually disappointed in you,

350
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,200
 he wants to hear about that.

351
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:11,480
 All that shame that you feel for what you did,

352
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:15,760
 that habit or addiction that you constantly hide in secret

353
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,640
 and you can't seem to upend,

354
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:19,800
 he wants you to come and talk to him about it.

355
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:22,520
 Like, that weariness you feel from your depression

356
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:24,040
 that no matter how hard you pray,

357
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:25,520
 no matter how much you trust,

358
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:29,240
 no matter how much you surrender, still seems to never end.

359
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:31,640
 God's like, "Come talk to me about it.

360
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:34,860
 "Come be honest with me about it, I know already.

361
00:13:34,860 --> 00:13:36,380
 "So just let me ask you then,

362
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:39,680
 "like what's keeping you from talking to him?

363
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:43,600
 "What's keeping you from being real with him?

364
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,600
 "What's keeping you from being honest?"

365
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,840
 I think for many of us,

366
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:49,800
 if I were just to kind of throw out a singular answer,

367
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:53,920
 though I know there's a variety of exceptions here,

368
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,840
 I know that generally speaking,

369
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:58,400
 the reason we don't talk to God honestly

370
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:00,640
 about the things that we struggle with,

371
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:05,120
 are frustrated by is because for fear of being wrong,

372
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,900
 we never come real.

373
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:08,800
 We don't wanna be wrong in the sight of God.

374
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:12,700
 And so what we do is we come completely fake.

375
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:15,040
 We look phony, we act false in front of him.

376
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:18,120
 And yet that's not the way that Abram does it.

377
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:20,880
 Abram comes completely honestly.

378
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:22,660
 And yet I love that as you read this,

379
00:14:22,660 --> 00:14:25,120
 you see he doesn't come disrespectfully.

380
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:28,080
 He calls him Lord God, that word Lord God,

381
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,880
 it's the word Adonai Yahweh.

382
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,960
 It's similar to what we talked about earlier in the series.

383
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,720
 But the idea here is he looks at God and he says,

384
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:37,160
 "Hey, you're Adonai.

385
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:38,880
 "You're my master, you're my Lord,

386
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:41,400
 "you're the sovereign supreme over everything.

387
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,280
 "And then at the same time, you're Yahweh.

388
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:44,800
 "You have a personal relationship with me.

389
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,440
 "I know your name."

390
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:49,580
 And so he comes and he is respectful to him.

391
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:51,160
 He acknowledges who God is.

392
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:54,440
 And yet though he is respectful, he is simultaneously real

393
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:55,280
 with him.

394
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:59,960
 Which we agree is possible, don't we?

395
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:02,580
 Like, isn't this the idea of tough love?

396
00:15:02,580 --> 00:15:07,400
 That someone would just deal straight with you,

397
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,940
 even if it's hard to receive for your own good.

398
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:13,280
 I know that this is what happens every morning

399
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,000
 when I come out of the bedroom and I look at Brooke

400
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,040
 and I say, "Hey, does this look okay?"

401
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:18,360
 And if she tells me no,

402
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:20,920
 I don't think it's because she hates me.

403
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,720
 Or is trying to sabotage my street cred.

404
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:24,360
 I think it's because she loves me

405
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,920
 and she's trying to save my street cred.

406
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:30,160
 She's being honest for my good.

407
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,000
 And because she, and the reason why

408
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,560
 is because she respects me.

409
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:37,560
 You can be honest with God because you respect him.

410
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:40,960
 You see, honesty is a way of honoring someone.

411
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:41,920
 And so the first thing you gotta do

412
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:43,600
 is you gotta come real to him.

413
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,320
 You gotta be honest with him.

414
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,800
 Again, I'm not telling you to rip,

415
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:51,200
 like to just kind of pop off on him or be disrespectful

416
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,120
 because the two of you were in very different weight classes

417
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:54,120
 and you can't handle that son.

418
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,280
 And yet what you do need to know

419
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:59,800
 is you can come very legitimately sincere

420
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:01,440
 if in fact you find yourself frustrated

421
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:02,600
 with something in life.

422
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:06,420
 Now, does that mean that he owes you an answer?

423
00:16:06,420 --> 00:16:08,240
 If you come and you ask him questions,

424
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,520
 does that mean that he's gonna tell you

425
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:11,620
 everything you wanna know?

426
00:16:11,620 --> 00:16:13,400
 No, it's interesting.

427
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,280
 Abram comes and he does ask God a question.

428
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:18,680
 And yet what you see is God gives him the silent treatment.

429
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:21,900
 Like he does not give him a reply at all,

430
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:23,560
 so much so that when you get to verse three,

431
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:25,800
 it's like the beginning of a new dialogue.

432
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,600
 It says, "And Abram said,

433
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:29,820
 "Behold, you've given me no offspring

434
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:32,100
 "and a member of my household will be my heir.

435
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:35,480
 "And then finally, behold, the word of the Lord came to him.

436
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:36,880
 "This man shall not be your heir.

437
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:39,320
 "Your very own son shall be your heir."

438
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:43,920
 Why doesn't God answer Abram the first time?

439
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:47,480
 Like he shows up and he asks a legitimate question.

440
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,880
 Why does God choose to plead the fifth

441
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:51,220
 and not engage with him?

442
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:53,780
 For this reason,

443
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:56,520
 you don't have to understand everything to trust God.

444
00:16:56,520 --> 00:17:01,840
 You don't have to understand everything to trust God.

445
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,120
 He doesn't owe you an answer

446
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:05,800
 because an answer doesn't make him trustworthy.

447
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:08,460
 His character does.

448
00:17:08,460 --> 00:17:10,720
 Like if you've ever wondered,

449
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:13,040
 like, God, why aren't you answering my questions?

450
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:14,700
 Why, God, aren't you answering my prayers?

451
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,960
 I'll tell you why he isn't.

452
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:17,800
 It's because you're not ready for it.

453
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:21,160
 It doesn't mean that he wants to leave you

454
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,360
 where you are for long.

455
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:25,680
 Maybe he's trying to grow something up in you

456
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:28,840
 or maybe he's trying to grow something out of you.

457
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:31,140
 But if he's not answering your questions,

458
00:17:31,140 --> 00:17:32,480
 responding to your prayer,

459
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:37,000
 it may be because he's wanting to do something in you

460
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,640
 before he does something through you.

461
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:41,120
 You just may not be ready yet,

462
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:45,520
 which ironically is exactly Abram's situation.

463
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,880
 Abram, he asks God, doesn't reply.

464
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:49,880
 He asks again and God's like, okay, fine.

465
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,520
 You want to know, guess what?

466
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:53,200
 Your heir shall be your own son.

467
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,000
 He tells Abram for the very first time,

468
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:59,400
 specifically where the blessing will come from.

469
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:01,300
 It's not through a general descendant.

470
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:03,160
 It's not through his offspring.

471
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,960
 It's not through some seed.

472
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:07,120
 It's through his son.

473
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:09,920
 And what you see is Abram takes this information

474
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:15,600
 and he absolutely ruins his story with it

475
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:18,280
 because he does not choose to receive that news

476
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:21,560
 and trust God by continuing to remain faithful to his wife

477
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:23,000
 who has a barren womb.

478
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:26,960
 Instead, he decides to take matters into his own hands

479
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:29,760
 and he sleeps with his servant, Hagar.

480
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:33,180
 And what he does is he prolongs the fulfillment

481
00:18:33,180 --> 00:18:36,100
 of God's promise by 12 years.

482
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:38,760
 You see, God knows, hey, you may not be ready

483
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:41,240
 for the information that I'm wanting to give to you.

484
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:44,880
 And we need to trust him that that may, in fact, be true.

485
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:45,760
 Like, it's fascinating.

486
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:48,840
 God called Abram to follow him in Genesis 12.

487
00:18:48,840 --> 00:18:51,740
 And when you look at it, five different times,

488
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:54,000
 he tells him, hey, all of the promises

489
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:57,760
 that I'm giving to you, they're not gonna come through you.

490
00:18:57,760 --> 00:18:59,060
 They're gonna come through me.

491
00:18:59,060 --> 00:18:59,900
 We see it.

492
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:02,440
 He says in chapter 12, he says, I, talking about God,

493
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:04,320
 I will show you the land.

494
00:19:04,320 --> 00:19:05,720
 I will make you a great nation.

495
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:07,200
 I will give you a name.

496
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:11,560
 I will bless you and I will curse those who dishonor you.

497
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:12,880
 So then let me ask you this,

498
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:15,320
 because I think it's gonna finally make its way home

499
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,840
 for us here in the room.

500
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:20,040
 Why doesn't Abram choose to trust in God?

501
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:23,560
 Why does he take matters into his own hands in this moment?

502
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:26,760
 If he has God's promise, if he knows what God's going to do,

503
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:29,600
 why then does he circumvent the process?

504
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:34,240
 Not because he doesn't think God can do it,

505
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:37,440
 because he doesn't think God will do it.

506
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:40,840
 You see, he questions his character,

507
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:43,400
 which feels really shameful to say out loud.

508
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,680
 Like we all hear that and we're like, how dare he do that?

509
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:47,960
 And yet we all do this

510
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:50,800
 in the secrecy of our private lives, don't we?

511
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,900
 We all look at the things that God has said,

512
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:55,280
 and in some way, and at some time,

513
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:58,400
 we feel like we're the exception to that rule.

514
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:01,280
 So yeah, sure, like God has come, or Christ has come

515
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:03,840
 that you might have life and have life abundantly,

516
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:06,200
 but that may be true for everybody else.

517
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:08,360
 But the thing is, like, you don't know my family,

518
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:12,280
 you don't know my history, you don't know my hope.

519
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:13,680
 Like, you're not gonna be able to lead me

520
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:15,560
 into abundant life because you haven't seen

521
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:16,600
 the mess that I've made.

522
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:19,240
 Or we know his promise to work all things together

523
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,080
 for the good of those who love him

524
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:21,280
 and are called according to his purpose.

525
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,000
 Except we look at us and we're like, dude,

526
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,840
 have you seen the mistakes that I've made?

527
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:27,320
 How wrong I've gone?

528
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:28,760
 There's no way back for me.

529
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:29,840
 That may work for other people.

530
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:30,960
 That's not gonna work for me.

531
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:32,400
 I'm the exception to that.

532
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:35,040
 Or we know the reality that nothing can separate us

533
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:37,480
 from the love of God, but the truth of the matter is,

534
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,200
 Jesus, you don't know what I've done.

535
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:43,240
 You don't know how deep the stain actually goes.

536
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:45,480
 And so we look to God and we claim

537
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:47,000
 what Abraham claims in this moment.

538
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,760
 We say that we're the exception.

539
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:51,520
 But here's the thing.

540
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:54,160
 There are no exceptions to God's promises.

541
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:56,800
 Every promise in the scripture

542
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:59,400
 for those that believe in Christ,

543
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,480
 those promises are true for them.

544
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:04,320
 And that includes you.

545
00:21:04,320 --> 00:21:06,160
 That's why God shows up in this moment

546
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:07,400
 and he rebukes Abraham.

547
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:10,360
 Like he shows up and he says, behold, that word behold,

548
00:21:10,360 --> 00:21:13,080
 it's the idea of, hey, whoa, hold up.

549
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:14,560
 Like he's trying to get Abraham's attention.

550
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:16,320
 I'm like, hey, wait, you're off track.

551
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:19,160
 Let's get back on track because what you're saying is crazy.

552
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,320
 It doesn't make any sense.

553
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:24,560
 And I love that it says the word of the Lord came to him.

554
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,240
 It's the first time that language,

555
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:28,520
 the word of the Lord ever appears in the Bible.

556
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:30,480
 And the reason it appears in this moment

557
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:33,680
 is it's the word of the Lord that Abraham forgot.

558
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:36,240
 And so that word comes to him.

559
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:39,040
 And here's the truth for us tonight.

560
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,160
 Many of us, we don't trust God

561
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:43,400
 because he hasn't told us the answers

562
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,680
 to the questions that we've been asking.

563
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:46,960
 And because that's true,

564
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:49,400
 we let our feelings tell us who he is

565
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:52,200
 rather than letting his word do all the talking instead.

566
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:55,000
 Like it's typical.

567
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,520
 I visit with people all the time.

568
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,360
 I myself was one of them.

569
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:03,880
 We get so hung up on God's unrevealed will.

570
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,520
 Like those things that are out in the future,

571
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:06,640
 which we know nothing about.

572
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,800
 What am I gonna do for my job?

573
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:08,640
 Who am I gonna marry?

574
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:09,680
 Are they the one?

575
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,440
 God, am I always gonna struggle like this?

576
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,520
 Am I ever going to get over this pain?

577
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:14,880
 Am I ever going to find God

578
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:17,000
 that this shame actually is subdued?

579
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:20,560
 We start asking all of these questions about the future.

580
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:22,920
 And what we do being so focused

581
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:24,720
 on the unrevealed will of God

582
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:27,560
 is we forget about the revealed will of God.

583
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:29,480
 We become so transfixed

584
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:31,520
 on what's gonna happen in the future

585
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:33,800
 that we forget what God has said about the past,

586
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,040
 even though it was he who was in the past

587
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:37,160
 that has everything to say

588
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:39,080
 about what's happening in your future.

589
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:45,640
 You see, so many of us, we struggle to trust God

590
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,840
 because the truth of the matter is

591
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:49,240
 we're willing to come to God

592
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:51,080
 and maybe we're even honest with God,

593
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:52,680
 but we don't want to receive

594
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:57,200
 God's honest word in return to us.

595
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,240
 We want to say our piece,

596
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:00,360
 but then we don't want to receive

597
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:03,160
 what he has to say in response.

598
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:06,000
 And yet the reality is there's no relationship

599
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,680
 in that sort of situation.

600
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:11,840
 God has much he wants to say to us.

601
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:15,360
 And that's why we've got to get into this book.

602
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:18,040
 That's why we've got to spend time in this word.

603
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:20,600
 Like this is not just an archaic text,

604
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:23,680
 something locked away long ago from a time well spent.

605
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:27,400
 No, this is a book that is speaking live today to you.

606
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:28,240
 It's relevant.

607
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,760
 It is a timeless truth.

608
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:31,600
 And so you need to read its words.

609
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,240
 You need to marinate in its scriptures.

610
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:35,720
 You need to spend time learning what it says

611
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:38,400
 because these are not just principles to know.

612
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:41,440
 This is evidence as to who God is.

613
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:45,000
 And the reason you find yourself struggling to trust in God

614
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,040
 is because you're questioning his character.

615
00:23:47,040 --> 00:23:48,200
 And he's like, no, no, no, no, no.

616
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:49,800
 Don't question my character.

617
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:51,520
 Remember who I am.

618
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:53,560
 Yeah, your circumstances may be sideways.

619
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:56,360
 Things may feel crazy, but the truth of the matter is

620
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:59,000
 everything can be falling apart, but I'm not.

621
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:00,960
 I'm still in control.

622
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:02,240
 I'm still sovereign supreme.

623
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:03,400
 I'm still on my throne.

624
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,880
 You can trust in me.

625
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:07,640
 And so we've got to be willing.

626
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:12,000
 We got to be willing to admit the fact

627
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,320
 that we don't have to understand everything to trust him.

628
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:20,520
 That's why God tells Abram to do what he does next.

629
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,880
 Because even though we have doubt,

630
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:24,320
 there is something that we can do with it.

631
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:26,600
 It says in verse five, and he brought him outside

632
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:28,600
 and he said to him, "Hey, look toward heaven

633
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:31,600
 "and number the stars if you're able even to number them."

634
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:35,040
 And then he said, "Hey, so shall your offspring be."

635
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,200
 And Abram believed the Lord

636
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:38,520
 and he counted it to him as righteousness.

637
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:39,640
 I love this.

638
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:43,760
 God looks at Abram who is questioning his character

639
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:46,240
 and knowing that, hey, you're struggling to trust me

640
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:47,080
 in this moment.

641
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:49,760
 God, he doesn't plead his innocence.

642
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:53,600
 He doesn't grovel for him to understand.

643
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:57,520
 Because God knows, okay, if it's my character in question,

644
00:24:57,520 --> 00:25:01,480
 character is not proven by way of what I say.

645
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:03,480
 Character is proven by way of what I do.

646
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:06,440
 Like you can say you're kind,

647
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:11,520
 but you actually convince someone that you are

648
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:13,080
 whenever you take the time to talk to them,

649
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:15,240
 even if it means you got to go out of your way.

650
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:17,240
 You can say you're humble,

651
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:19,920
 but it's way more convincing to lavish praise

652
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:20,800
 upon other people,

653
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:23,600
 even though you did the majority of the work.

654
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,960
 Like you can say that you're reliable,

655
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:29,560
 but it's way more convincing to actually follow through

656
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:30,680
 on the promises you make.

657
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:32,360
 See how that works?

658
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:33,960
 It's why when you apply for a job,

659
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:35,200
 they want character references.

660
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,560
 Why do they want character references?

661
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:39,280
 Because they may be able to get a good impression of you,

662
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:42,160
 but they cannot ascertain the quality of your character

663
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:43,200
 in a single interview.

664
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:44,040
 They've got to talk to people

665
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:45,440
 that have spent time with you,

666
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:46,480
 because the truth of the matter is,

667
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:50,760
 character is proven through consistent evidence over time.

668
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:52,720
 And so that's why God takes Abram and he's like,

669
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,440
 "Let's go look at the stars."

670
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:59,280
 Because he knows, Abram stands before those stars.

671
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:02,520
 He and we will remember who you're dealing with.

672
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:05,800
 You'll remember who you're dealing with.

673
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:06,920
 It's the third thing you got to do

674
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:11,120
 if you want to build a relationship of trust with God.

675
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,000
 Like, I love it.

676
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:15,400
 He doesn't come to Abram all punitively.

677
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:16,320
 He doesn't look at him and say,

678
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:18,160
 "Okay, son, you're going to doubt me?

679
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:20,080
 Let's step outside and take a look at those.

680
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:20,920
 What do you think of them?

681
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:22,040
 You want to go ahead and start counting them?

682
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:24,320
 Yeah, you want to be real serious about this?"

683
00:26:24,320 --> 00:26:26,400
 He doesn't do that with them.

684
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:28,800
 He takes Abram and he does.

685
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:33,000
 He walks him out and he says, "Hey, look up.

686
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:40,200
 I put all of those where they are.

687
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:42,480
 I'm the star maker.

688
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:46,720
 The scriptures say that God breathed them into existence.

689
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:50,040
 I'm the creator of the cosmos.

690
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:52,200
 If I can do that,

691
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:55,680
 don't you think I can take care of your boy?

692
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:59,040
 Don't you think I can provide for you a son?"

693
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:01,600
 I love it.

694
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,400
 David in Psalm 8,

695
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:05,800
 he references a similar sort of situation

696
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:07,600
 where he had to come face to face

697
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:09,480
 and gain a new perspective on who God was.

698
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:13,240
 And the way that he did was by looking at the night sky.

699
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,080
 That says in verse three,

700
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:15,960
 "When I look at your heavens, the work of your fingers,

701
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:17,760
 the moon and the stars, which you've set in place,

702
00:27:17,760 --> 00:27:20,280
 what is man that you're mindful of him?

703
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:22,560
 The son of man that you care for."

704
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:24,840
 I think that's why God tells Abram to step outside

705
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:25,680
 and look at the stars,

706
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,240
 not just because he wants him to get to counting,

707
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:29,600
 because he wants him to get a new perspective.

708
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:34,160
 You see, he wants Abram to go from

709
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,280
 telling God all about his problems

710
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:40,840
 to telling his problems all about his God.

711
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:43,560
 He wants to shift his perspective.

712
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:44,520
 Now, the truth of the matter is,

713
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:46,600
 I know it's not feasible for all of us to do this,

714
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:48,400
 to jet set to some desert nearby

715
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,800
 and get underneath the night sky

716
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:52,040
 and look at the cosmos above.

717
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:53,520
 I know that that's not feasible for us,

718
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:55,840
 but yet it is feasible for us

719
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,520
 to block some time on the calendar,

720
00:27:57,520 --> 00:27:59,320
 to take a day off work,

721
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:02,080
 to set aside some time every single month

722
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:07,080
 so that way we can not only work for God,

723
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:09,200
 but we can actually walk with God.

724
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:13,240
 I remember as a student in college,

725
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:15,960
 I would sit on the front steps

726
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:18,120
 of the administration building at Texas A&M,

727
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:21,960
 and it was there that I regularly found myself

728
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:24,840
 meeting with God,

729
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:26,480
 and under the night sky there,

730
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:30,320
 learning who he was and what he was like,

731
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:31,880
 what his heart beat for,

732
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:33,480
 what, in fact, he cared about,

733
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:35,280
 what he had to say about me,

734
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:36,120
 and what it looked like for me

735
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:38,440
 to actually internalize those truths.

736
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:42,160
 It was by way of me setting aside time to be with him

737
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:44,840
 that I was able to learn who he was

738
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:46,760
 and thus who I am.

739
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:48,960
 God wants to do the same thing for you.

740
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:52,320
 The truth is, we just don't often set that time aside,

741
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:54,560
 but it's much easier to do than we think.

742
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:57,480
 We just gotta commit ourselves to doing it.

743
00:28:57,480 --> 00:29:01,360
 And the thing is, when we do this,

744
00:29:01,360 --> 00:29:03,120
 what happens is our trust rises,

745
00:29:03,120 --> 00:29:04,940
 because even when we can't make sense

746
00:29:04,940 --> 00:29:08,480
 of the world around or the situations

747
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:09,760
 we find ourselves suffering through,

748
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:11,040
 we can still look at God and say,

749
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:14,380
 man, this may all feel like chaos, but you don't.

750
00:29:14,380 --> 00:29:17,560
 This may all feel disordered, but you aren't.

751
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:19,760
 You, God, are still good.

752
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,320
 And so even though it may feel like

753
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:25,120
 all of my reality is spinning into disarray,

754
00:29:25,120 --> 00:29:27,080
 you, God, are still here,

755
00:29:27,080 --> 00:29:28,840
 you, God, are still good,

756
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:32,080
 and you, God, are still committed to me.

757
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:36,400
 Which, interestingly, is where this story ends.

758
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:38,960
 We see in verse six

759
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:42,280
 that Abram believed in God

760
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,760
 and it was counted to him as righteousness.

761
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:48,040
 And so he believes in God according to his character.

762
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:49,960
 Again, God takes him out, shows him the stars,

763
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:54,960
 and it evidences to Abram who God is.

764
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,060
 And yet as we keep going,

765
00:29:57,060 --> 00:29:59,000
 we find ourselves in this moment

766
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,240
 that is honestly kind of strange.

767
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:02,840
 Like, you read through it and you're like,

768
00:30:02,840 --> 00:30:04,640
 what is happening here?

769
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:08,480
 And yet God wants to ratify not only his character,

770
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:11,400
 but also his commitment to Abram and to ourselves.

771
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:13,720
 So it says this in verse seven.

772
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:15,200
 And he said to him,

773
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:18,080
 I'm the Lord who brought you out from Ur of the Chaldeans

774
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:20,840
 to give you this land to possess.

775
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:22,360
 But Abram said, oh, Lord God,

776
00:30:22,360 --> 00:30:25,280
 how am I to know that I shall possess it?

777
00:30:25,280 --> 00:30:27,920
 And he said to him, bring me a heifer three years old,

778
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:30,240
 a female goat three years old, a ram three years old,

779
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:31,520
 a turtle dove, a young pigeon.

780
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:32,560
 See how it gets odd?

781
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:36,960
 And he brought him all these and he cut them in half.

782
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,600
 Gets a little bit more odd.

783
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:41,560
 And he laid each half over against the other,

784
00:30:41,560 --> 00:30:43,280
 but he didn't cut the birds in half.

785
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:45,640
 And when the birds of prey came down on the carcass,

786
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:46,960
 Adam drove them away.

787
00:30:46,960 --> 00:30:48,520
 The Bible is just odd sometimes.

788
00:30:48,520 --> 00:30:49,840
 You know, you read this stuff and you're like,

789
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:51,500
 what on earth is happening?

790
00:30:51,500 --> 00:30:54,700
 There's good reason for why all of this is happening.

791
00:30:54,700 --> 00:30:56,960
 Because while admittedly we have no category

792
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,640
 for what's happening in this text,

793
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:00,140
 Abram does, you see it.

794
00:31:00,140 --> 00:31:02,560
 Like God starts asking random stuff

795
00:31:02,560 --> 00:31:03,560
 and Abram's like, yes, sir.

796
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:05,160
 And he just starts going and he finds the animals

797
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,120
 and he starts cutting them in half

798
00:31:06,120 --> 00:31:07,600
 and he starts splitting the pieces.

799
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:10,880
 Clearly he understands what God has asked and we do not.

800
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:12,140
 So it begs the question,

801
00:31:12,140 --> 00:31:14,120
 what was happening in their context

802
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:17,840
 to help us realize what in fact this means?

803
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:19,680
 Well, Abram knows the minute God starts giving

804
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:21,440
 all the instructions, what God is wanting to do

805
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:24,760
 is he is wanting to set up a blood path covenant,

806
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:28,200
 which was a ritual ceremony in the ancient Near East

807
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:30,680
 where two parties would enter into an agreement

808
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:33,160
 with one another and they would walk through the pieces

809
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:37,960
 of these animals one after the other, testifying

810
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:40,920
 to each other that if they don't keep their oath,

811
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:45,560
 as was done to this animal, so shall it be done to me.

812
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:47,720
 It's declaring a consequence

813
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:49,820
 if they fail to keep their commitment.

814
00:31:49,820 --> 00:31:53,940
 And the reason God does it with Abram in this moment

815
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:57,440
 is because he knows, Abram, he's questioning,

816
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:58,940
 hey, can I trust you God?

817
00:31:58,940 --> 00:32:02,440
 And so God looks at him by way of his own suggestion

818
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:07,240
 and he's like, hey, let's make a covenant,

819
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:09,600
 get the animals, you know what to do.

820
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:12,400
 And the reason for it is fourthly,

821
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:14,240
 you can only trust God's character

822
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:17,080
 if you can trust God's character

823
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:19,300
 when you can trust God's commitment to you,

824
00:32:19,300 --> 00:32:22,840
 when you trust God's commitment to you.

825
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:25,280
 It's fascinating.

826
00:32:25,280 --> 00:32:27,760
 This idea of covenant, it can feel distant to us,

827
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:29,960
 but we experience this today,

828
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:33,600
 the primary place where we see covenant in our modern world

829
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:35,800
 is in the form of marriage.

830
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:37,840
 I know for Brooke and I, we talk often

831
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:39,960
 about the covenant of marriage that we share

832
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:42,240
 with one another, not because we'd love to reminisce

833
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:44,400
 on that day long ago that was so very wonderful,

834
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,720
 though I think we did in fact have the best wedding.

835
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:47,880
 We talk about that covenant

836
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:49,680
 because we often got to rely on it.

837
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:52,280
 Like we look at each other and I'll do something stupid

838
00:32:52,280 --> 00:32:53,600
 or she'll say something she regrets.

839
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:56,440
 And we're like, God, I'm so thankful for this covenant

840
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:57,800
 because the truth of the matter is,

841
00:32:57,800 --> 00:33:02,600
 even though we're untrustworthy towards one another,

842
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:06,160
 I can believe by way of your commitment to me

843
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:08,880
 before God and all our family and friends

844
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,360
 that you're not going anywhere.

845
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:14,320
 You see, there's something in a commitment to another person

846
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:19,320
 that allows us to find a deep level of trust.

847
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:21,800
 And so that's what God's trying to do with Abram right now.

848
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:24,240
 He's like, hey, I wanna give you even more reason to trust.

849
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:28,320
 I've given you enough, like my character is flawless.

850
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:29,560
 There's nothing concerning about me.

851
00:33:29,560 --> 00:33:30,920
 There's no questions you could ask

852
00:33:30,920 --> 00:33:32,760
 that would ever bring me into any kind of reproach.

853
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:34,560
 Like I don't lie, I don't cheat.

854
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:35,960
 I don't steal, I don't sin.

855
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:38,520
 Like God is perfectly good.

856
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:39,920
 And yet he looks at Abram and he's like,

857
00:33:39,920 --> 00:33:44,680
 but so you have even more reason.

858
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:45,980
 Let's make this covenant,

859
00:33:45,980 --> 00:33:49,520
 which is really interesting to think about.

860
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:51,520
 The fact that God is the one who suggests it

861
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:52,760
 because here's the truth.

862
00:33:52,760 --> 00:33:57,040
 Covenants, they're used as a sort of safeguard

863
